1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Web accessibility is a legal requirement,
but most open source projects never get audited.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,500
Manual testing is slow, expensive,
and rarely done.

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:14,500
a11y-forge changes that.

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:22,768
It is an autonomous scanner that checks any
GitHub repo against WCAG standards in seconds.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Here is how it works. Paste any public
GitHub repository URL, like this one, and click Scan.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,000
a11y-forge pulls the source tree via the GitHub API,
runs 12 static WCAG checks across HTML, JSX, CSS, and Vue files.

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
And scores the repo from A-plus to F.
The progress bar shows each stage.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:50,984
Scanning, prioritizing violations by impact,
and generating results.

9
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Results are shown immediately. The score card
gives you a clear grade with a breakdown of violations by type.

10
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Each violation shows the file, line number,
severity, and a confidence score.

11
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:08,000
The screen reader preview simulates how these
issues affect assistive technology users.

12
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:13,344
You can drill into every finding
to understand exactly what needs to be fixed.

13
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:18,000
The documentation covers everything you need,
quick start guide, full API reference with curl examples.

14
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:24,000
And a detailed scanner reference showing all
12 WCAG check types from color contrast to keyboard traps.

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:31,720
The project includes HTML and PDF report generation,
and SVG badge creation.

16
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:37,000
a11y-forge is open source, built during
OpenAI Build Week 2026 using Codex CLI.

17
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,000
The runtime uses OpenAI GPT-5.6 to intelligently
group violations by user impact.
Codex accelerated development with conversational coding.

18
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Try it yourself. Paste any public repo URL
and see your score in seconds.

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:54,720
Every open source project
deserves to be accessible.
